		"description": "<p>A Medium or smaller object becomes invisible, as do any inanimate contents inside it when the spell is cast. Objects removed from the spell&rsquo;s original target become visible. Objects placed in or on the target after the spell is cast remain visible, and dirt, dust, and other markings may reveal the invisible object&rsquo;s location. The spell ends if the object deals damage.</p>\n<p>Attacks made with an invisible melee weapon are made with advantage.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Cast at Higher Levels</em>: </strong>When cast with a 5th-level spell slot, the duration is 1 day. When cast with a 7th-level spell slot, the duration is permanent until dispelled.</p>",
